<img class="aligncenter wp-image-1317073" src="https://i1.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/MAP-2.jpg?resize=600%2C582&#038;ssl=1" alt="" width="600" height="582" srcset="https://i1.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/MAP-2.jpg?w=228&amp;ssl=1 228w, https://i1.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/MAP-2.jpg?resize=58%2C56&amp;ssl=1 58w, https://i1.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/MAP-2.jpg?resize=200%2C194&amp;ssl=1 200w, https://i1.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/MAP-2.jpg?resize=134%2C130&amp;ssl=1 134w" sizes="(max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px" data-recalc-dims="1" /> At least 14 people have died and four injured after an Improvised Explosive Device (IED) blew up a bus in north-western Burkina Faso. The vehicle was mainly carrying students back to their places of study after the New Year break. Reports suggest the bus drove over the IED in Toeni, a department in the region of Sourou. It is not clear who was behind the attack but the jihadist threat has increased in Burkina Faso recently. 35 civilians including 31 women were killed on Christmas Eve in the north of the country in a suspected jihadist attack on a military base. Western countries have attempted to help governments in the region combat insurgents, but the violence has continued. (BBC)  Vanguard Five people, four of them police, were killed when their vehicle struck an improvised explosive device (IED) in Burkina Faso, security sources said Saturday. December 1, 2018 In "News" Four people were killed Sunday at a Catholic church in northern Burkina Faso in the latest in a series of attacks on Christian targets in the region, according to a bishop in the region and a security source. May 26, 2019 In "News" Burkina Faso is declaring a state of emergency in provinces grappling with jihadist violence, Communications Minister Remis Fulgance Dandjinou said on Monday. December 31, 2018 In "News"